<HEADLINE>
USC TO HOST FIRST-ROUND REGIONAL
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   &LR; LOS ANGELES _ The defending national champion USC baseball team
will host a four-team, first-round regional May 28-30, the NCAA
announced Monday.
</P>
<P>
   The Trojans (33-23) were one of 16 schools selected to host a
round-robin, double-elimination regional in the expanded 64-team
playoffs. Stanford is the only other West Coast site for the first
round. The tournament field will be announced Monday.
</P>
<P>
   A tournament pass for the USC regional is $50, and single-game
tickets are $10. For more information, call (213) 740-4672.
</P>
