r s &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BKN-LAKENOT-LADN-(SLA     05-18 0449
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-LAKENOT-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
KOBE IS ADVISER TO YOUNG STARS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SAN ANTONIO _ Kobe Bryant is only 20 years old, but the
third-year veteran has become a mentor to underclassmen of the NCAA
and would-be teen-age NBA stars.
</P>
<P>
   Rhode Island sophomore Lamar Odom declared himself eligible for
the NBA draft on Monday but not before consulting with the Lakers'
young phenom, who decided to turn pro three years ago at the tender
age of 17.
</P>
<P>
   For Bryant, already an All-Star and a starter on one of the
NBA's best teams, the move has obviously turned out to be a good
decision. But for every Bryant, there are the Jermaine O'Neals
(Portland) and Tracy McGradys (Toronto) who struggle with the
adjustment.
</P>
<P>
   So when Bryant's hit up for advice, he offers a conservative
approach.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's different for every individual,'' he said, ``but when
they ask for your advice or what you think, you can only tell them
about certain things you experience. You can't tell them what to do
or what not to do because everyone's different. Some people, it
works out fine, some people it doesn't.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's really a gut feeling. At least for me it was,'' Bryant
said. ``I just knew it was the right thing. I couldn't explain why
or come up with concrete reasons. It just felt right.''
</P>
<P>
   Odom, 19, and Bryant have been friends for years, having run in
the same youth-league circles.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think he was just looking for experiences, certain things to
look forward to, what to expect, what not to expect. A lot of the
same things I was looking for,'' Bryant said.
</P>
<P>
   Bryant's a success story among early entries, but he said his
rookie season, when he barely played, was tough.
</P>
<P>
   ``It can be a great move depending on the individual,'' he said.
``Personally, I think if I was a different person, my rookie year
would have been miserable, because I didn't play that much, I went
through a lot of ups and downs, a lot of criticism, stuff like
that. But it's how you handle it, it's how you take it.''
</P>
<P>
   So his words of wisdom to Odom were simple: ``Have fun and
learn. That's all. Be patient.''
</P>
<P>
   ``I told him, `Welcome to the league _ I'll be waiting to give
you 40.''
</P>
<P>
   __ Glamour boys: The Lakers will be victims of their own
popularity this weekend. To get them on NBC as much as possible,
the league has scheduled back-to-back Games 3 and 4, Saturday and
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
   ``I don't know if it's ever happened before, so I don't know if
it's good or bad,'' coach Kurt Rambis said. ``That's something
that's out of my and everybody's else's control. You just deal with
it the best you can.''
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
