<SLUG> BC-USBANK-KAN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
INTRUST FINANCIAL CORP. TO BUY KANAS U.S. BANCORP BRANCHES 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  
 By CHARLES R.T. CRUMPLEY  
 c. 1999 Kansas City Star  
<TEXT>
<P>
   KANSAS CITY, Mo. _ Intrust Financial Corp., which has had a low
profile in the Kansas City area even though it is the largest bank
holding company in Kansas, is poised to increase its strength in
the area.
</P>
<P>
   Intrust has agreed to buy 20 Kansas branches now owned by U.S.
Bancorp, based in Minneapolis. The locations include three suburban
branches.
</P>
<P>
   Intrust now has two suburban branches and a grocery store
branch.
</P>
<P>
   Intrust, with $2.1 billion in assets, is dominant in its
headquarters of Wichita but is weak in the Kansas City area.
</P>
<P>
   Intrust spokeswoman Diane Iseman said the company was looking
for ways to step up its presence in Johnson County, as well as in
the college towns of Manhattan and Lawrence, when ``this deal kind
of fell in our lap.''
</P>
<P>
   The deal was offered by U.S. Bancorp, which operates banks under
the name U.S. Bank. It entered Kansas in 1995 but never caught
fire. Its market share was too small to effectively sell its
products and services in Kansas, said a spokeswoman in Minneapolis.
U.S. Bancorp also said it planned to sell eight branches in Iowa.
</P>
<P>
   Under the deal, Intrust will buy all of U.S. Bancorp's branches
in Kansas, including all $275 million in deposits, but not the
loans. Most branches are in the eastern half of the state, in towns
such as Emporia, Iola and Topeka. It is likely that four branches
in Wichita and one in El Dorado will be closed, Iseman said.
</P>
<P>
   The branches will continue to operate as U.S. Banks until the
sale is completed by about September.
</P>
<P>
   U.S. Bancorp is the country's 14th-largest holding company, with
$76 billion in assets. It is also known for its purchase a year ago
of Piper Jaffray Cos. Inc., now known as U.S. Bancorp Piper
Jaffray, the 11th-largest brokerage.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
