<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    FIGHTING ON THE KOSOVO-ALBANIA BORDER
 &HT;    With KOSOVO-BORDER-0519.
 &HT;    By CHARLES W. HOLMES 
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service 
<TEXT>
<P>
   AT RISK IN ALBANIA:
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Serb forces have been shelling and snipers firing on the
following towns and villages:
</P>
<P>
   Krume, Golaj, Dobrune, Vlahem, Qarri.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Serb forces occupy positions just inside the Albanian border
near the village of Letaj, near Krume.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Albanian and Serb forces have clashed near the border town of
Pogaj, just north of the main border crossing for refugees at
Morina.
</P>
<P>
   THE KLA REGROUPING:
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Main KLA training camp for 1,000-1,500 troops at Helshun
(halfway between Kukes and Bajram Curri). Another in Kukes and
small camps spread throughout the border area.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Operational headquarters for forays into Kosovo at Barjam
Curri. Force strength unknown.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Political and recruiting effort at Kukes, and in the nearby
refugee camps.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Main fighting between KLA and Serbs, near Tropoje, on the road
from Barjam Curri to the border with Yugoslavia. Last week, Serbs
made their deepest foray yet, about one-half mile, capturing the
border town of Perroi I Thanes and Kasaj.
</P>
<P>
   YUGOSLAV ARMY STRENGTH
</P>
<P>
   Yugoslav Army positions on the border with Albania. (prior to
start of NATO's air campaign):
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  Two infantry companies and SA-6 surface-to-air missiles in
Djakovica.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  One tank company near Decane.
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  In addition, for the past week NATO jets have been hitting the
hills near Zur, about 2 miles from the main border crossing at
Morina. The targets are believed to be tanks and heavy artillery
hidden in the forests.
</P>
