   WITH: BOOK NEWS: It's something of a relief to pick up the first
four volumes in a new series of books, biographies of 150 pages or
so, well written by people who know. The series is called ``Penguin
Lives,'' and at first glance it might be seen as a kind of
biographical literature for the age of the sound bite.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: REVIEW: CRYPTONOMICON: Neal Stephenson's ``Cryptonomicon''
is filled with technical information about the minutiae of
code-writing and breaking, statistics and probability theory and
encryption within various computer programs. There's a plot mixed
in there, too. (Includes 1-column B&AMP;W photo of author as a child
and a 6-pica color photo of book jacket.)
</P>
