<HEADLINE>
A MODEL ROSE 
</HEADLINE>
   (af)  
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   Simi Rose of Cabernet Sauvignon, 1997, California. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   There has been renewed interest in rose wines in recent years.
It's a good thing, too, because rose _ decent rose _ can be a
welcome relief from heavier red wines in the warm months. People
are getting past the misapprehension that roses are wimpy.
</P>
<P>
   In fact, there is no reason a lighter-bodied wine can't have
intense flavors and bouquet. This wine is elegant, as are the Anjou
roses of the Loire Valley. Those are made from cabernet franc; Simi
makes this one from cabernet sauvignon.
</P>
</TEXT>
