SAN FRANCISCO _  &UR; TASTE-Cookie Dough  &LR; _ This week, The Chronicle's
panel of professional tasters rates prepared cookie dough. &QL; 
 &UR; By Robin Davis &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; c. 1999 The San Francisco Chronicle &QL;  &LR; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
SOUTH SAN FRANCISCO, Calif. _ &UR; CLASSIC-Gimbal Bros. Inc. &LR;  _ You may
not recognize Gimbal candy by name, but have you bought the jelly
candies at See's? Or the licorice at the candy shop in FAO Schwarz
at Union Square in San Francisco? Then Gimbal has sated your sweet
tooth.
</P>
<P>
   From sour worms, gum balls and ``Ultimate'' jelly beans to Gummy
Mummies, Nonpareil Hearts and Christmas Sour Stars, Gimbal Bros.
Inc. produces 3 million pounds of the chewy, gel-based candies each
year &QL; 
 &UR; By Maria Cianci &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; c. 1999 The San Francisco Chronicle &QL;  &LR; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
SAN FRANCISCO _  &UR; QUICK-Salmon Fillets  &LR; _ From its richly textured,
wonderfully flavored meat to its silvery blue-black skin that could
inspire the House of Versace, salmon is among the world's most
aristocratic fish.
</P>
<P>
   But when it comes to cooking, salmon doesn't require fancy
handling.
</P>
<P>
   With recipes, sidebar on leftovers. &QL; 
 &UR; By Maria Cianci &QL;  &LR; 
 &UR; c. 1999 The San Francisco Chronicle &LR;
