<HEADER>
A1922 &Cx1f; ttx-z
r l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A-TEX     05-18 0736
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
AN ERUPTION OF INFORMATION
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q: How many volcanoes, active or dormant, are there in the
continental United States?
</P>
<P>
   _ W.P., N. Richland Hills, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: The World Wide Web site Volcano World lists 68 that aren't in
either Alaska or Hawaii.
</P>
<P>
   Volcanoes are found in Arizona (9), California (10), Idaho (3),
New Mexico (10), Oregon (23), South Dakota (1), Utah (2),
Washington (8) and Wyoming (2).
</P>
<P>
   ``About 10 percent of the more than 1,500 volcanoes that have
erupted in the past 10,000 years are located inthe United
States,'' according to the Cascades Volcano Observatory in
Washington.
</P>
<P>
   Volcano World, which is published at volcano.und.edu, tracks
current volcanic activity. The most recent event in the continental
United States was a series of small earthquakes and the release of
carbon dioxide at Mount St. Helens in June 1998.
</P>
<P>
   ``It is possible that the current earthquake activity may
eventually lead to renewed volcanic activity,'' according to the
Cascades observatory.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Whatever happened to the woman who shot Andy Warhol in the
'60s?
</P>
<P>
   _ P.C., Albany, N.Y.
</P>
<P>
   A: Valerie Solanas, a feminist writer who had appeared in
Warhol's film ``I, a Man,'' died of pneumonia in 1988 at age 52.
</P>
<P>
   Solanas shot Warhol on June 3, 1968, after blaming him for
problems related to a book contract she had signed. ``It's not
often that I shoot somebody. I didn't do it for nothing,'' she said
at her arraignment.
</P>
<P>
   The incident was the focus of a 1996 film, ``I Shot Andy
Warhol.''
</P>
<P>
   After shooting Warhol in front of several witnesses, Solanas
pleaded guilty to first-degree assault and served three years
before her release. She was destitute at the time of her death in
San Francisco.
</P>
<P>
   Q: How many Kool-Aid flavors are there?
</P>
<P>
   _ M.C., Fort Worth
</P>
<P>
   A: When Edwin Perkins introduced the drink powder Kool-Ade in
1927, there were originally seven flavors: Cherry, Grape,
Lemon-Lime, Orange, Raspberry, Root Beer and Strawberry.
</P>
<P>
   In the United States, Kraft Foods sells all these Kool-Aid
flavors today except Raspberry and Root Beer, according to a list
compiled by the Internet discussion group alt.drink.kool-aid.
</P>
<P>
   These flavors are also available: Black Cherry, Blastin' Berry
Cherry, Grape Berry Splash, Ice Blue Island Twist, Ice Blue
Raspberry Lemonade, Lemonade, Lemonade Tea, Tangerine,
Man-O-Mangoberry, Oh-Yeah Orange-Pineapple, Pink Lemonade, Roarin'
Raspberry Cranberry, Slammin' Strawberry-Kiwi, Soarin'
Strawberry-Lemonade, Strawberry Tea, Tropical Punch,
Watermelon-Cherry and Wildberry Tea.
</P>
<P>
   To contact Kraft Foods for more information, call (800) 367-9225
or visit the World Wide Web site www.kool-aid.com.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I heard that NBC is going to do away with ``Another World.''
When is the last day it will be broadcast?
</P>
<P>
   _ G.B., Burleson, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A: NBC will air ``Another World'' for the last time on June 25,
35 years after the soap premiered on May 4, 1964.
</P>
<P>
   The network canceled the show in April to make room for
``Passions,'' a new soap that will begin airing July 5.
</P>
<P>
   ``Another World'' fans are encouraging Procter &AMP; Gamble, which
produces the soap, to find a new network or syndicate the show
rather than halt production in late May. To contact the company,
write to Robert Wehling, Procter &AMP; Gamble, 1 Procter &AMP; Gamble
Plaza, Cincinnati, OH 45202.
</P>
<P>
   The National Enquirer is collecting letters to send to NBC about
the cancellation. To participate, write to ``Another World,''
National Enquirer, Lantana, FL 33464-0002.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can I write to Sarah Michelle Gellar of ``Buffy the
Vampire Slayer''?
</P>
<P>
   _ D.S.B., Clifton, N.J.
</P>
<P>
   A: Write to Gellar or any of her co-stars in care of ``Buffy the
Vampire Slayer,'' Warner Bros. Television Network, 4000 Warner
Blvd., Burbank, CA 91522.
</P>
<P>
   The 22-year-old actress broke her wrist during this season's
filming of ``Buffy,'' which concludes May 22. After starring in
five movies since the TV series began, Gellar has not announced
whether she'll take on any new projects this summer.
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com)  &QL; 
nn
</P>
