<P>
   (NYT10) SEKONOS, Macedonia -- May 18, 1999 -- KOSOVO-REFUGEES-2,
5-18 --Newly arriving ethnic Albanian refugees from Kosovo look
from their bus at a refugee camp on Tuesday. About 1,000 ethnic
Albanians crossed into Macedonia Tuesday and aid agencies said
refugees were now being driven out of Kosovo not only by Serb
terror but also by fear of starvation. (Andrew Testa/New York Times
Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT5) SEKONOS, Macedonia -- May 18, 1999 -- KOSOVO-REFUGEES-1,
5-18 -- Newly arriving ethnic Albanian refugees from Kosovo try to
revive a woman who fainted on a bus arriving at a refugee camp on
Tuesday. (Andrew Testa/New York Times Photo) LITE
</P>
