<P>
   PRERUNNER _ Car shoppers who think of the venerable Honda Civic
as a bastion of practical and reliable _ but unexciting _
transportation are going to be surprised by the new Civic Si. The
car is a truly worthy successor of the recently departed CRX and
the Si models of the early and mid-1980s. (DeVault, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) Art includes 3-column color photograph of the
1999 Honda Civic Si.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: AT A GLANCE _ Fact box previewing the 1999 Honda Civic Si.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: SHARP DRIVING _ Cars are not the only inhabitants of our
roadways. Pedestrians also share our streets and with the weather
getting warmer and days longer, we can expect to see more people
out walking and exercising. Here are a few suggestions to improve
the safety on our roads. (Carter, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
Includes 1-column color photograph of columnist.
</P>
<P>
   SHARP-DRIVING _ ATLANTA _ If having it all is what a true
premium luxury car is really all about, then Mercedes-Benz's
S-Class may be on a page by itself. The totally new body design
2000 S-Class boasts one of the most extensive lists of safety,
performance, comfort and convenience features. (Sharp, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) MOVED
