<P>
   WINSCOTT RANCH, Texas _ Chocolate Chip and Carrot Top, two
massive longhorn steers who led the 1995 Great American Cattle
Drive to Miles City, Mont., are vying for a place in the Fort Worth
Herd to be introduced June 12 at the city's sesquicentennial
celebration. Four new steers arrived at the Winscott Ranch
southwest of Fort Worth on Friday. Chocolate Chip and Carrot Top
were shipped from Sallisaw, Okla., along with two other steers, one
of which also carries the Circle 95 brand from the Great American
Cattle Drive. By ART CHAPMAN. Story has moved in ``a'' general news
