<P>
   UNDATED _ About 70 percent of the drugs used in children _ from
asthma medications to Prozac and Ritalin _ have never been tested
in children. But that changed April 1 when the FDA began requiring
that new drugs with potential to benefit children be tested in
children and labeled as safe and effective for use in children. By
CAROLYN POIROT. Story has moved in ``l'' lifestyle category. &QL; 
