   DRUGS-SAMPLES &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ Since they became legal two years ago, TV and radio
commercials have taken a big bite out of advertising budgets, but
pharmaceutical companies still spend most of their promotional
funds _ $2.5 billion last year _ marketing directly to doctors. But
the distribution of drug samples is now regulated by both the Food
and Drug Administration and the ethics policies of professional
medical organizations. By CAROLYN POIROT. Story will move in ``l''
lifestyle category. &QL; 
