 &UR; CALPERS _  &LR; Negotiators for the California Public Employees'
Retirement System recommended that the pension fund let health
insurers raise premiums an average of 9.7 percent next year for its
members. The proposal calls for Kaiser, Calpers' biggest
contractor, to raise rates 11.7 percent. Foundation would be
allowed to raise rates 9.9 percent. Calpers, whose premiums rose an
average of 7.3 percent this year, is the first big purchaser of
health benefits to set premiums for next year. By Arthur M. Louis
