helplessly as a fellow student shot and killed three other
teen-agers and wounded his younger brother Craig at a Kentucky high
school in December 1997. Keene recounted his experiences before a
House Education subcommittee that was holding a forum on school
shootings. By JENNIFER CORBETT DOOREN. (Already filed.)
</P>
