<HEADLINE>
ABC CHANGES INCLUDE MOVIES ON SATURDAYS, SIX NEW SERIES IN FALL 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By JOHN LEVESQUE  
 c.1999 Seattle Post-Intelligencer  
<TEXT>
<P>
   ABC, famous for placing good shows on Saturdays and then
canceling them after nobody watched, will address the problem next
fall by eliminating all series on Saturday nights in favor of
three-hour movies.
</P>
<P>
   The network on Tuesday said it will introduce six new shows next
fall, three comedies and three dramas. It also will move ``Dharma &AMP;
Greg'' from 8 to 9 p.m. on Wednesdays and ``Spin City'' from 9 to 8
p.m. on Tuesdays.
</P>
<P>
   Here's a summary of ABC's new prime-time series:
</P>
<P>
   Snoops. The latest from David E. Kelley is about private eyes
who bend the rules on the road to justice. Best character name
(from Kelley, the hockey fan): Glenn Hall, played by Gina Gershon.
</P>
<P>
   Once and Again. ``NYPD Blue'' always starts its season late, so
this romantic drama will begin in the Tuesday-at-10 slot. After
that? ABC isn't saying. It's about two divorced parents trying to
re-learn dating skills. Best character name: Slim pickings here,
but we'll go with Zoe.
</P>
<P>
   Oh Grow Up. Three guys, a girl and no pizza place in this
ensemble comedy. One of the guys is gay; the girl is the daughter
of one of the guys. Best character name: Hunter.
</P>
<P>
   Wasteland. Hourlong drama about six twentysomethings trying to
make it in New York City. Best character name: Tossup between
Dawnie, a grad student, and Vandy, a struggling musician.
</P>
<P>
   Then Came You. ABC calls this a romantic comedy with a twist.
She: a 34-year-old book editor. He: a 24-year-old room-service
waiter. Best character name: Aidan, the waiter.
</P>
<P>
   Odd Man Out. From the writers of ``There's Something About
Mary'' comes this half-hour comedy about a 14-year-old boy living
with his mom, his aunt and his three sisters. Best character name:
ABC only revealed the name of the male character, Andrew, but two
of the actresses have neat names: Natalia Cigliuti and Marina
Malota.
</P>
<P>
   ABC's prime-time lineup for next fall (Times listed are Seattle
time):
</P>
<P>
   SUNDAY
</P>
