President Clinton and Vice President Al Gore during an event at the
Pentagon last year. After years of battling with President Clinton,
House Republicans are shifting their sights to Vice President Gore
and using ridicule as their weapon of choice. Armey's office has
become a clearinghouse of anti-Gore press releases and activity,
with the Texas Republican mocking the Vice President and Democratic
presidential contender over his pronouncements on air travel, the
Internet and urban traffic congestion. (Justin Lane/New York Times
Photo)
