shipment of wine. At this moment they are on a collision course
with an explosion in direct marketing of wine and other spirits
through catalogs, wine clubs and the Internet as consumers have
turned into aficionados. One of the unintended consequences has
been the growth of an industry in California that barely existed a
few years ago: third-party shipping of wine. (Igor Vishnyakov/New
York Times Photo)
