<HEADLINE>
NEW YORK TIMES CORRECTIONS FOR WEDNESDAY, MAY 19
</HEADLINE>
 Eds.: These corrections will appear in The New York Times on
Wednesday. Days and dates refer to the original article's
transmission by the New York Times News Service, and may need to be
adjusted by NYT clients.)  
(gc) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   BC-HOLBROOKE-CONFIRM-NYT (moved on Tuesday, Apr. 20)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Tuesday, Apr. 20,
about an investigation into Richard C. Holbrooke's nomination as
chief American diplomat at the United Nations referred incompletely
to a speaking fee. Mr. Holbrooke's financial disclosure filings
with the State Department included the information that he spoke to
the Siemens electronics company in October 1998 for a $24,000 fee.
But on April 22 Mr. Holbrooke amended his filing to show that the
speech had been canceled and no fee paid.
</P>
<P>
   BC-SPORTING-GOODS-INTERNET-NYT (moved on Sunday, May 9)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, May 9,
about an electronic commerce venture backed by several sporting
goods retailers misstated the name of a comparable Internet site
supported by wine and spirits wholesalers. It is wineshopper.com,
not -wineshipper.com.
</P>
<P>
   BC-YOUNG-ACTORS-NYT (moved on Sunday, May 9)
</P>
<P>
   A New York Times News Service article sent on Sunday, May 9,
about television networks' efforts to find young actors for new
youth-oriented shows included an outdated reference to ``Roswell,''
which is about teen-age space aliens. After the article went to
press, the Fox network said it had decided not to use the show,
which will now be seen on the WB network.
</P>
</TEXT>
