u a &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-FORBES-SEATTLE-SPI &LR;      05-18 0775
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FORBES-SEATTLE-SPI </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
FORBES MAGAIZINE RANKS SEATTLE NO. 1 IN GROWTH OF `NEW ECONOMIES' 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By ARTHUR C. GORLICK  
 c.1999 Seattle Post-Intelligencer  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SEATTLE _ You did it again, Seattle. A major magazine ranks you
No. 1 in the nation.
</P>
<P>
   This time, Forbes magazine says Seattle topped 162 metropolitan
areas in growth in jobs, income and output in the area's high
technology industries, including aerospace, computer software,
biotech, telecommunications, Internet companies and others.
</P>
<P>
   The city leads the nation in growth in this ``new economy,''
based on brainpower, as opposed to the ``old economy,'' based on
