said.
</P>
<P>
   ``Seattle's preeminence is a reflection of its momentum, its
breadth of technologies it has sustained during its growth and
prosperity during the 1990s,'' Ferguson said.
</P>
<P>
   The magazine also examined average wage and salary increases and
average job growth in high-tech industries in the two most recent
years available ``to catch the most recent momentum,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   Perry Wong, a Milken Institute research associate who helped
